Busia senator Amos Wako has joined other Luhya leaders to dismiss the planned Bukhungu western leaders meeting organized by the COTU secretary general Francis Atwoli.Wako claims leaders from the region have not beenÂ  consulted and that the meeting is aimed at benefiting few individuals. The senator expressed fears that the meeting might be used by some individuals to divide the region further at the expense of strengthening political and economic well-being. Be was speaking at Budokomi secondary school in Matayos constituency